Strong response language

Applicant respectfully submits that the cited portions do not establish a prima facie case of obviousness.

US 10,459,887 Claim 1 is directed to pre-launching an application when an icon satisfies position-based pre-launch criteria. Claim 8 adds displaying contextual information for icons in a zoomed-in view. US 2019/0339860 A1 ¶¶ 0231–0233 disclose complications moving between predefined watch-face locations, changing size, and displaying different amounts of information based on location size.

Accordingly, the cited portions teach only position/size-based display of additional or contextual information. They do not disclose or suggest the claimed [Applicant to insert missing claim features].

Even if the cited portions are combined, the combination would at most yield an icon or complication that displays additional information based on position, zoom, or location size. The combination would not yield the claimed technical architecture. Therefore, the cited portions do not support the §103 rejection, and withdrawal of the objection is respectfully requested.